## BNK-001: Secure Login

**User Story:** As a customer, I want to log in securely so that I can access my bank account.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
1. Login requires username and password
2. Two-factor authentication is available
3. Invalid credentials show error
4. Password is encrypted
5. Session timeout after inactivity

**Generated Test Cases:**

| ID | Type | Preconditions | Input | Steps | Expected Result | Covered AC |
|----|------|---------------|-------|-------|-----------------|------------|
| TC01 | Positive | Account exists | Valid credentials | 1. Enter username/password<br>2. Click login<br>3. Verify access | Access granted | AC1, AC4 |
| TC02 | Negative | Invalid password | Wrong password | 1. Enter invalid password<br>2. Click login | Error message | AC1, AC3 |
| TC03 | Boundary | Maximum login attempts | 5 attempts | 1. Attempt login 5 times<br>2. Account locked | Account locked | AC1, AC3 |
| TC04 | Exception | Network error | Login during outage | 1. Simulate network error<br>2. Attempt login | Error handled | AC1 |
| TC05 | Concurrency | Multiple users | Simultaneous login | 1. Multiple users login<br>2. Concurrent sessions | All logged in | AC1, AC4, AC5 |

**Coverage:** 5/5 (100%)

